OL,3,C'One of Britain's greatest': Tributes
OL,4,Cpour in after death of Bonnie Tyler
OL,6,FTyler was born in Skewen, Neath, in
OL,7,FSouth Wales, the daughter of Glyndwr
OL,8,FHopkins, a coal miner, and his wife,
OL,9,FElsie (nee Lewis), and grew up in a
OL,10,Fcouncil house with three sisters and
OL,11,Ftwo brothers.
OL,13,FShe grew up listening to Frank
OL,14,FSinatra, Elvis Presley and the Beatles
OL,15,F` although her favourites were Janis
OL,16,FJoplin and Tina Turner - and had a
OL,17,Fdeeply religious background, attending
OL,18,Fchapel three times a day on Sundays.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
